{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"158602a7-b8f4-4d4d-91b4-0feb27ba80c8","content":"Yes, both are known MSTest v4 breaking changes. Here's a summary:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Lost test history in Azure DevOps\n\nMSTest v4 changed the **default test-ID generation strategy**. Azure DevOps tracks tests by ID, so every test looks \"new.\" To restore history, add this to your `.runsettings`:\n\n```xml\n<MSTest>\n  <TestIdGenerationStrategy>Legacy</TestIdGenerationStrategy>\n</MSTest>\n```\n\nOr keep the new IDs and accept a one-time history reset.\n\n---\n\n### 2. `TestContext.TestName` in `[ClassInitialize]` throws\n\nIn v4, the `TestContext` passed to `[ClassInitialize]` is now **class-scoped** — it has no associated test. Accessing `TestName` (line 13 of your file) throws because no individual test is running yet.\n\n**Fix:** remove that access from `ClassInit`, or guard it:\n\n```csharp\n[ClassInitialize]\npublic static void ClassInit(TestContext context)\n{\n    // context.TestName is not available here in v4\n    // Move per-test logic to [TestInitialize] instead\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Other key v4 breaking changes to watch for\n\n| Area | What changed |\n|---|---|\n| **`[ClassInitialize]`/`[ClassCleanup]` inheritance** | Now inherited by default. Derived classes no longer need `InheritanceBehavior.BeforeEachDerivedClass` — it's the default. If you set it explicitly, verify behavior. |\n| **`TestContext.Properties`** | No longer writable from test code; attempts to add/modify throw. Use a different mechanism to pass state. |\n| **Parallel execution** | Now enabled by default at the **method** level. Tests that relied on implicit sequential execution may break with concurrency bugs. Opt out via `[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.ClassLevel)]` or disable entirely. |\n| **`Assert.AreEqual` for collections** | Floating-point and collection comparisons have stricter semantics. Review any assertions that were \"accidentally\" passing. |\n| **Removed deprecated APIs** | `Assert.That` and some legacy overloads were removed. You'll see compile errors for these (sounds like you already resolved them). |\n\n---\n\n### Quick action items for your project\n\n1. Add a `.runsettings` with `Legacy` test-ID strategy (or accept the reset).\n2. Move `context.TestName` usage on **line 13** of `SetupTests.cs` to a `[TestInitialize]` method.\n3. Verify your test suite isn't relying on sequential execution — run with `--logger console;verbosity=detailed` and watch for flaky failures.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4f85d994-1409-4354-afc1-23683e597950","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about MSTest v4 breaking changes. Let me address each concern:\n\n1. **Tests appearing as brand new in Azure DevOps (lost history)**: In MSTest v4, the default test ID generation changed. MSTest v3 used a legacy fully qualified name-based ID, while v4 uses a new stable ID scheme. This means Azure DevOps sees them as completely different tests, losing history. The fix is to set `<TestIdGenerationStrategy>` to `Legacy` or use the MSTest runner's configuration.\n\n2. **`TestContext.TestName` in `[ClassInitialize]`**: In MSTest v4, the `TestContext` passed to `[ClassInitialize]` is a class-level context, not tied to any specific test. \n\nSo accessing `TestContext.TestName` throws `NotSupportedException` because there's no individual test associated with class-level initialization—this is a deliberate behavioral change in v4.\n\n3. **Other things to watch out for**: The inheritance behavior for `[ClassInitialize]` and `[ClassCleanup]` changed, `TestContext.Properties` is no longer writable by default, async lifecycle methods are now preferred, `DeploymentItem` behavior shifted, and several deprecated APIs were removed.\n\nThe Azure DevOps test history issue stems from how MSTest v4 generates fully qualified test IDs differently by default. Let me provide clear guidance on what's happening and how to address it.","outputTokens":1081,"requestId":"0C0B:37135:B65560:D27186:69F023E7"},"id":"b935b335-62e1-4ae3-b338-ec9f198d7651","timestamp":"2026-04-28T03:05:37.079Z","parentId":"ae9537a5-5801-4dac-b5eb-5d408341fb8b"}
